The paper discusses serverless computing, which is a cloud-native paradigm for deploying applications and services. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the programming models and abstractions used in serverless computing, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the technical challenges and open problems in serverless computing, which falls under the category of Distributed Systems (cs.Distributed). The paper also mentions the delegation of operational complexity to cloud providers, which falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper briefly mentions the potential use of serverless computing in augmented reality (AR) applications, which falls under the category of Computer Graphics (cs.AR).
